post_text: Families with students in grades K – 5 who are currently in Enhanced Distance Learning (EDL) will need to commit to a preferred method for learning. Please check your email for details from your child’s school on how to inform us of your choice. We need your decision submitted by 5 pm on Sunday, September 13. If you don’t submit a commitment form, your student will be placed in the phased-in, full-return model and follow the schedule, which can be found at http://bit.ly/SUSDreturnschedule.

post_text: We’d like to make sure that you know that SUSD is still in the “yellow” health metric benchmark. This means that we are still in Enhanced Distance Learning (remote learning) for most students. We need 2 weeks of “green” metrics in all 3 categories (see www.susd.org/Metrics for details) to be able to transition to a full return to on-campus learning. That being said- we do meet the ADHS metrics for what they name “hybrid” learning – which means for SUSD – that we are in the early stages to bring some students back on campus. Special Education students will be the first group to be on campus. Want to know more? Tune in to a special meeting of the Governing Board on our YouTube channel on 9/9 at 5 pm. They will be discussing next steps and how to possibly phase in on campus learning in grade-level cohorts. We invite you to go to the direct source of SUSD metrics as posted on our website at www.susd.org/Metrics. This week’s detailed spreadsheet of metric analysis by zip code is found here: http://bit.ly/94Metrics.

post_text: The Governing Board of the Scottsdale Unified School District (SUSD) concluded at its Sept. 1 Special Meeting that it wants to hear from parents first, before it decides how to pursue a reopening of SUSD school campuses. The Governing Board will convene at 5 p.m., Sept. 9 in a special meeting to review parent feedback and the most recent health metrics. For a copy of the meeting agenda, visit www.susd.org/Board. The meeting will be broadcast live and will also be available for replay on the District’s official YouTube channel.

post_text: Scottsdale Unified’s Operations and Logistics Health and Safety subcommittee will be working to identify recommendations for metrics to be used in determining when it is safe to reopen our schools based on the guidance provided by the Arizona Department of Health Services. They will formulate a recommendation for consideration at the Aug. 18 regularly scheduled Governing Board meeting. The Maricopa County Department of Public Health will have a dashboard, updated weekly, that will include data for each of the three areas identified by the Arizona Department of Health Services guidance metrics. They will be able to provide data on the positivity rates by school district and zip code so we can make informed decisions on reopening. We continue to work daily to demonstrate our commitment to the health, safety, and wellbeing of our students and staff.
text: Scottsdale Unified’s Operations and Logistics Health and Safety subcommittee will be working to identify recommendations for metrics to be used in determining when it is safe to reopen our schools based on the guidance provided by the Arizona Department of Health Services. They will formulate a recommendation for consideration at the Aug. 18 regularly scheduled Governing Board meeting. The Maricopa County Department of Public Health will have a dashboard, updated weekly, that will include data for each of the three areas identified by the Arizona Department of Health Services guidance metrics. They will be able to provide data on the positivity rates by school district and zip code so we can make informed decisions on reopening. We continue to work daily to demonstrate our commitment to the health, safety, and wellbeing of our students and staff.

post_text: Congratulations, Carick! #ProudSUSDFamily
shared_text:
Desert Mountain High School SUSD
August 1 at 1:49 PM ·

Desert Mountain's Carick Veale earned a spot on the National Honor Choir! Students from all over the United States, auditioned by recording their own entry. The concert is held during the National Association of Music Educators National Convention! What an honor for Carick and Desert Mountain!

The process is very personal for each candidate! It's about these students, at this time, in this place. post_text: “National Board process boils down to a teacher's desire to put their practice up for review to represent standards reflective of accomplished teaching for the betterment of their students. The process is very personal for each candidate! It's about these students, at this time, in this place. That's why teachers and their students get so invested in the process,” Susan Leonard – National Board Certified Educator, Ingleside Middle School. www.susd.org/NBCT
